text: Leslie Pye (6 July 1871 - 9 March 1949) was an Australian cricketer. He played 29 first-class matches for New South Wales between 1896/97 and 1905/06. ==See also== * List of New South Wales representative cricketers ==References== ==External links== * Category:1871 births Category:1949 deaths Category:Australian cricketers Category:New South Wales cricketers Category:Cricketers from Sydney
